document_data.History:
Qirozz predated Zariel's rise to power in Avernus and managed to keep her position as a tactician even after she took over the layer.{{Cite adventurers league/Consequences of Choice|27}}

Eons ago, Qirozz was locked in combat with [[adventurer]]s who summoned to their aid the [[hound]]-headed [[angel]] [[Verwyr]]. In the end both the adventurers and the angel were slain, and Qirozz decided to strip the flesh from the celestial and fashion its skull into the Fetid Chalice.{{Cite adventurers league/The Breath of Life|2}}

Somewhere around the late 15{{th}} century [[DR]] the Fetid Chalice became unusable for Qirozz, for any liquid poured into it became [[holy water]]. Unbeknownst to Qirozz, fragments of Verwyr lingered on within the goblet, and she was responding to a supernatural "call from on high" for aid. The duchess persisted with her parties despite the chalice's condition,{{Cite adventurers league/The Swarmed Heart|4}} Using her [[divine]] powers, Dara returned the long-dead angel to life with a kiss on the forehead.{{Cite adventurers league/The Breath of Life|9}}

When she learned of the theft of the chalice, she destroyed all the furniture of one of her rooms in a rage, eventually calming down while remaining highly annoyed by the robbery and worried about the hit to her prestige. As such, she sought a new prize or noteworthy deed to complete to restore her damaged reputation.
